requires a variety of strategies. Women's movements all over the world today are critically creating new models of self and society in their own contexts. Drawing on notions of Beauvoir, as well as Michel Foucault, this book outlines a 'feminism in a new key' which consists of women's various freedom practices, each hunting the Hydra in their own key - but with mutual support.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFeminismvCross-cultural studies. 0aFeminismxHistory. 0aMale domination (Social structure) 0aMale domination (Social structure). 0aWomenxSocial conditions. 0aWomen's rights. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUrban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019z978311063851640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048522279?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048522279zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048522279/original  a978-3-11-060644-7 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-063851-6 Urban Studies and Social Rights eBook Package PP 2016-2019c2016d2019  a978-3-11-066284-9 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8 AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c